1
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:04,959
(Fight for You)

2
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:09,370
People always say that good and evil cannot coexist.

3
00:01:10,930 --> 00:01:13,280
But can the right and the wrong

4
00:01:13,340 --> 00:01:15,070
be absolute?

5
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:19,450
Whether we're a match or not,

6
00:01:19,450 --> 00:01:20,850
we decide for ourselves.

7
00:01:22,580 --> 00:01:24,440
There is a kind of willingness...

8
00:01:25,480 --> 00:01:27,680
that exists because that person is you.

9
00:01:30,080 --> 00:01:31,860
There's a kind of persistence that lasts until the end

10
00:01:31,860 --> 00:01:33,390
because that person is you.

11
00:01:35,690 --> 00:01:41,020
(File 10: I Won't Give Up on You)

12
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:44,940
You still changed the bandages for me.

13
00:01:45,610 --> 00:01:48,380
That means even if you're angry,

14
00:01:49,240 --> 00:01:51,039
you'll still forgive me, right?

15
00:01:51,650 --> 00:01:52,650
I admit,

16
00:01:53,170 --> 00:01:55,970
at first, I approached you with ulterior motives.

17
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:58,789
But I don't know when it started—

18
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:01,580
watching you work so hard for Grandma

19
00:02:01,810 --> 00:02:03,850
and for Jiali,

20
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:06,680
I started to hate who I was.

21
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:10,729
So I wanted to quickly help you finish the task

22
00:02:10,830 --> 00:02:12,130
and end everything.

23
00:02:13,570 --> 00:02:16,800
But somewhere along the way, I fell for you.

24
00:02:20,180 --> 00:02:22,579
I wanted to tell you the truth many times...

25
00:02:24,780 --> 00:02:26,250
but I knew

26
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,800
that the moment I did,

27
00:02:30,550 --> 00:02:32,320
it would all be over between us.

28
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:56,140
Don't you want me anymore?

29
00:02:57,710 --> 00:02:58,940
Hei...

30
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:25,340
Just wait for me a little longer.

31
00:03:25,340 --> 00:03:26,170
At least let me say goodbye...

32
00:03:26,170 --> 00:03:28,300
You think he still wants to talk to you?

33
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:35,010
From renting this place

34
00:03:35,010 --> 00:03:37,540
to becoming his roommate to surveilling him—

35
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:41,250
from the very beginning, you two were destined to be on opposite sides.

36
00:03:41,250 --> 00:03:43,980
Now, you just say, “Sorry, it was for the mission.

37
00:03:44,130 --> 00:03:45,579
Let's just be friends?"

38
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:47,210
Bai Zhouqi,

39
00:03:47,610 --> 00:03:49,720
are you the idiot here, or is he?

40
00:03:56,610 --> 00:03:57,370
I don't know,

41
00:03:57,370 --> 00:03:58,690
and I don't want to know

42
00:03:58,710 --> 00:04:00,840
just how real your act with him became.

43
00:04:01,570 --> 00:04:03,570
But let me give you a piece of advice:

44
00:04:03,790 --> 00:04:05,720
don't challenge our grandfather.

45
00:04:19,930 --> 00:04:21,360
Stop struggling.

46
00:04:21,740 --> 00:04:23,340
Or you'll reopen your wound.

47
00:04:25,620 --> 00:04:26,450
Okay.

48
00:04:27,410 --> 00:04:28,720
I'll go pack up.

49
00:04:28,740 --> 00:04:29,600
No need.

50
00:04:30,110 --> 00:04:31,830
I'll send someone to pack for you.

51
00:04:31,830 --> 00:04:33,430
Don't keep Grandpa waiting.

52
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:34,409
Zhouguo...

53
00:04:34,470 --> 00:04:35,110
Let's go.

54
00:04:35,110 --> 00:04:36,280
