I told you

107
00:06:53,840 --> 00:06:55,900
not to go head-to-head with Grandpa.

108
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:14,380
Hei!

109
00:07:37,440 --> 00:07:38,380
Zhouguo.

110
00:07:39,310 --> 00:07:40,770
I'm here to get his things.

111
00:07:43,170 --> 00:07:44,510
Is Bai alright?

112
00:07:48,290 --> 00:07:50,750
Even if he wasn't, what could you do about it?

113
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:54,090
Don't be too hard on him. He's injured now.

114
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,840
You really care about him...

115
00:07:57,580 --> 00:07:58,650
and don't hate him?

116
00:07:58,940 --> 00:08:00,300
He lied to you.

117
00:08:03,030 --> 00:08:05,120
He's suffering just as much from having lied to me.

118
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:06,990
This job was never right for him.

119
00:08:07,910 --> 00:08:10,100
That's the mission of a man from the Bai family.

120
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:12,230
No one cares whether you want it or not.

121
00:08:12,390 --> 00:08:13,980
If he hadn't met you,

122
00:08:14,380 --> 00:08:16,840
he wouldn't be in such a difficult position.

123
00:08:17,190 --> 00:08:18,910
He had never been in a relationship before,

124
00:08:18,910 --> 00:08:20,570
and his sympathy runs wild.

125
00:08:20,790 --> 00:08:21,690
But you...

126
00:08:22,350 --> 00:08:23,680
you look tough enough.

127
00:08:24,220 --> 00:08:26,060
Hold back and don't contact him.

128
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:27,530
As time goes by,

129
00:08:27,550 --> 00:08:28,660
he'll forget.

130
00:08:43,169 --> 00:08:44,159
Hei,

131
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:46,220
the drinks in the fridge are all mine.

132
00:08:46,220 --> 00:08:47,150
You drink water.

133
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:50,860
I found it.

134
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:53,610
It was right underneath. How could you not see it?

135
00:08:54,460 --> 00:08:55,190
Look!

136
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:56,760
I managed to keep it alive.

137
00:08:56,790 --> 00:08:57,730
For you.

138
00:10:22,650 --> 00:10:25,340
We sent our Bai to the Intelligence Bureau all safe and sound,

139
00:10:25,340 --> 00:10:27,800
and now he returns home with a gunshot wound.

140
00:10:28,050 --> 00:10:28,850
Chief,

141
00:10:29,650 --> 00:10:31,450
don't you owe us an explanation?

142
00:10:42,940 --> 00:10:43,780
Forget it.

143
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,490
Seeing you like this

144
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:47,770
is worse than scolding you.

145
00:10:58,180 --> 00:10:59,820
You got beaten up too?

146
00:11:02,250 --> 00:11:03,490
It really hurts!

147
00:11:05,640 --> 00:11:08,500
You would have been beaten too if you had been there.

148
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:14,120
So, after all that trouble,

149
00:11:14,660 --> 00:11:15,720
did you catch them?

150
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:18,130
Yes.

151
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:22,740
The thing they were trading that day.

152
00:11:28,030 --> 00:11:29,270
Isn't this...

153
00:11:29,300 --> 00:11:30,730
Sweet potato starch!

154
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,870
Dou Keyi is really something.

155
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:40,090
My poor Bai took a bullet

156
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:42,450
for this small bag of sweet potato starch.

157
00:11:46,540 --> 00:11:47,570
Right,

158
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:49,240
how are you going to handle Hei Yubo?

159
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:50,240
What about him?

160
00:11:51,560 --> 00:11:54,690
He showed up at the scene with a box of sweet potato starch

161
00:11:55,010 --> 00:11:57,810
and was ambushed before he could do anything else.

162
00:11:58,320 --> 00:12:00,780
And your brother has defended him like that.

163
00:12:02,020 --> 00:12:04,150
So, I've asked Bai to deal with him.

164
00:12:06,410 --> 00:12:07,910
What a joke, right?

165
00:12:08,670 --> 00:12:09,510
Yeah.

166
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:13,040
Dou Keyi got away clean

167
00:12:13,280 --> 00:12:14,850
and even got the Intelligence Bureau

168
00:12:14,850 --> 00:12:17,780
to get rid of the man he was planning to double-cross.

169
00:12:18,940 --> 00:12:20,340
Two birds with one stone.

170
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:24,360
Dou Keyi really is a genius.

171
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:31,470
What?

172
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:37,860
Hand Dou Keyi's case to someone else.

173
00:12:38,340 --> 00:12:40,170
Do you know that you're mixing

174
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:41,930
in too many personal feelings?

175
00:12:42,860 --> 00:12:44,920
If it had been Dou Keyi standing there

176
00:12:44,970 --> 00:12:46,990
that day instead of Hei,

177
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:49,520
would you still have let them open fire?

178
00:13:14,850 --> 00:13:15,960
I heard

179
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:17,430
what you said outside my door that day.

180
00:13:17,430 --> 00:13:18,540
Are you okay?

181
00:13:19,980 --> 00:13:21,480
Shall we talk properly?

182
00:13:29,570 --> 00:13:31,210
Just remember

183
00:13:31,210 --> 00:13:32,940
that unfulfilled wish of mine.

184
00:13:36,550 --> 00:13:38,580
You promised me a wish!

185
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:42,040
Don't get involved with the convenience house anymore.

186
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:44,200
If you still want to be with me,

187
00:13:44,980 --> 00:13:46,320
then don't go.

188
00:13:56,150 --> 00:13:57,950
Why don't you eat?

189
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:01,400
You said

190
00:14:01,430 --> 00:14:03,220
as long as I cut ties with him,

191
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:04,710
you would leave him alone.

192
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:07,730
Why are you still having people investigate him?

193
00:14:07,890 --> 00:14:11,140
If he hasn't done anything wrong, why should he
be afraid of being investigated?

194
00:14:11,140 --> 00:14:13,480
Every time I mention that Hei guy,

195
00:14:13,510 --> 00:14:16,810
whatever I say, you argue back.

196
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,970
You're hopeless!

197
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:34,740
Tell me, what is all this?

198
00:14:35,190 --> 00:14:37,190
Was all of this just for the mission?

199
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:53,350
Isn't your boyfriend cool?

200
00:14:53,790 --> 00:14:56,180
It's great to have you.

201
00:14:56,210 --> 00:14:57,380
Don't forget,

202
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:59,630
you have a boyfriend now.

203
00:15:13,150 --> 00:15:16,970
I know. You have strong empathy.

204
00:15:18,020 --> 00:15:19,480
Combined with your guilt,

205
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:22,840
it's making you unable to move on.

206
00:15:23,070 --> 00:15:24,750
It's understandable.

207
00:15:24,780 --> 00:15:25,510
All right.

208
00:15:25,750 --> 00:15:27,180
The mission is done.

209
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:31,310
I failed the mission!

210
00:15:35,940 --> 00:15:38,280
Because I've fallen in love with him.

211
00:15:47,420 --> 00:15:50,380
It must be that Hei guy who taught you these bad ideas!

212
00:15:50,470 --> 00:15:51,580
Grandpa,

213
00:15:51,620 --> 00:15:52,980
I'm the cruel one.

214
00:15:53,010 --> 00:15:54,410
I'm the one who fell in love with him!

215
00:15:54,410 --> 00:15:55,250
Shut up!

216
00:15:57,170 --> 00:15:59,490
Both of you are men.

217
00:15:59,710 --> 00:16:01,040
What love?

218
00:16:01,270 --> 00:16:03,330
How can two men be together?

219
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:04,490
How inappropriate!

220
00:16:06,030 --> 00:16:07,690
Times have changed, Grandpa.

221
00:16:07,690 --> 00:16:09,300
Why can't we?

222
00:16:09,650 --> 00:16:11,020
Why can't my love for someone

223
00:16:11,020 --> 00:16:12,350
simply be accepted?

224
00:16:19,070 --> 00:16:20,240
Zhouguo, it hurts.

225
00:16:20,380 --> 00:16:22,050
Be gentler!

226
00:16:23,330 --> 00:16:25,020
Didn't you just act all tough earlier,

227
00:16:25,020 --> 00:16:26,550
not making a peep?

228
00:16:27,590 --> 00:16:29,030
That was different.

229
00:16:29,270 --> 00:16:32,070
In the heat of the moment, I had to hold it together!

230
00:16:36,610 --> 00:16:38,090
You're so brave, huh?

231
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:39,280
Is it worth it?

232
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:42,440
What if he doesn't want you anymore after all this?

233
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:44,210
Hei is not that kind of person.

234
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:49,430
You sure trust him, don't you?

235
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:53,490
How's Grandpa doing?

236
00:16:54,090 --> 00:16:56,250
Finding out you've fallen in love with your mission target—

237
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:57,650
and a man at that—

238
00:16:57,680 --> 00:16:59,220
is a huge shock

239
00:16:59,590 --> 00:17:01,830
for him.

240
00:17:01,860 --> 00:17:02,960
Do you understand?

241
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:09,400
I know it's hard for Grandpa.

242
00:17:10,369 --> 00:17:12,150
But a little bump

243
00:17:12,530 --> 00:17:14,369
won't dent a steel wall.

244
00:17:14,670 --> 00:17:17,140
If you want to break through, go big!

245
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:26,910
You...

246
00:17:27,690 --> 00:17:29,550
you look harmless on the outside,

247
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:30,480
but you're actually

248
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:32,680
the most stubborn one in our Bai family.

249
00:17:34,310 --> 00:17:35,530
You're already like this,

250
00:17:35,530 --> 00:17:38,330
and you're still going on a hunger strike protest?

251
00:17:39,770 --> 00:17:41,610
If only Hei were here.

252
00:17:44,490 --> 00:17:45,920
Sorry to disappoint.

253
00:17:45,950 --> 00:17:48,080
I'm not Hei.

254
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:14,060
I never thought

255
00:18:14,060 --> 00:18:15,990
I'd do this behind Grandpa's back.

256
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:18,530
I'm helping you not because I approve of you,

257
00:18:18,530 --> 00:18:20,130
but because our Bai Zhouqi

258
00:18:20,130 --> 00:18:22,200
is the type who never gives up once he's made up his mind.

259
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:23,440
I'm afraid if you ignored him,

260
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:24,510
he'd blame himself

261
00:18:24,510 --> 00:18:26,400
and might even come to resent others.

262
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:27,410
But I...

263
00:18:28,280 --> 00:18:31,010
I'm also afraid that he doesn't want to talk to me.

264
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:34,340
I'm more afraid that he'll run away from home because of you.

265
00:18:34,340 --> 00:18:37,200
If Grandpa really goes berserk, no one can stop him.

266
00:18:43,040 --> 00:18:44,540
He's really torn, too.

267
00:18:45,410 --> 00:18:47,540
Grandpa forced him to cut ties with you

268
00:18:47,820 --> 00:18:49,280
by offering to let you off.

269
00:18:49,670 --> 00:18:52,500
He's worried that you'll keep getting tangled up with the convenience house.

270
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:53,440
To be honest,

271
00:18:54,260 --> 00:18:55,240
you are just two kids

272
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:56,740
who know nothing.

273
00:18:57,520 --> 00:18:58,890
You two kids

274
00:18:59,010 --> 00:19:00,620
just behave yourselves for a while.

275
00:19:00,620 --> 00:19:02,340
Wait until we adults sort things out,

276
00:19:02,340 --> 00:19:05,070
and then you can date or break up however you like.

